---
export const prerender = false;
import HiddenGrammarLayout from '../../layouts/HiddenGrammarLayout.astro';
---

<HiddenGrammarLayout
  title="Reference Materials"
  description="The Feldman Four-Step Critique, Visual Arts Standards, and the foundational documents the Art Lab framework builds on."
>
  <div class="hg-page ref-page">

    <header class="ref-header">
      <p class="ref-label">Reference</p>
      <h1 class="ref-title">Reference Materials</h1>
      <p class="ref-subtitle">Foundational documents the Art Lab framework builds on. These are the structural predecessors—the frameworks Hidden Grammar extends, modifies, and in some cases departs from.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Feldman Four-Step Critique -->
    <section class="ref-section">
      <div class="ref-section-header">
        <span class="ref-section-tag">Method</span>
        <h2 class="ref-section-title">Feldman Four-Step Critique</h2>
        <p class="ref-section-desc">Edmund Burke Feldman's four-step framework is the standard structure for art criticism in educational settings. Art Lab's analysis modes adapt this structure—replacing Step 4 (Judgment) with a Growth Path and adding mechanism-based explanations grounded in perceptual science.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ref-steps">
        <div class="ref-step">
          <div class="ref-step-num">1</div>
          <div class="ref-step-body">
            <h3 class="ref-step-title">Description</h3>
            <p class="ref-step-note">Be 100% objective — think in facts only</p>
            <ul class="ref-step-list">
              <li>What specific Elements of Art (color, line, shape, texture, form, space, value) can you find within this piece?</li>
              <li>What's the title of the artwork?</li>
              <li>Who is the artist?</li>
              <li>When and where was it created?</li>
              <li>What media was used?</li>
              <li>Is there a primary subject in the piece?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ref-step">
          <div class="ref-step-num">2</div>
          <div class="ref-step-body">
            <h3 class="ref-step-title">Analysis</h3>
            <p class="ref-step-note">Be 100% objective — think in facts only</p>
            <ul class="ref-step-list">
              <li>What Principles of Art (balance, emphasis, movement, pattern, repetition, proportion, etc.) can you find within this piece?</li>
              <li>How do the Elements of Art interact with each other? Are there interesting visual effects created?</li>
              <li>What specific elements stand out in this composition and why? Is there a focal point?</li>
              <li>How is the work organized?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ref-step">
          <div class="ref-step-num">3</div>
          <div class="ref-step-body">
            <h3 class="ref-step-title">Interpretation</h3>
            <p class="ref-step-note">Subjective — requires thought on your part</p>
            <ul class="ref-step-list">
              <li>What is the artist trying to communicate?</li>
              <li>What thoughts or feelings come up when you see this piece?</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="ref-step-aside">Abstract works frequently require learning more about the context the work was created in (artist's life and time/place in history) in order to better understand them. Express your opinion, but always back it up with evidence.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ref-step">
          <div class="ref-step-num">4</div>
          <div class="ref-step-body">
            <h3 class="ref-step-title">Judgment</h3>
            <p class="ref-step-note">Subjective — requires thought on your part</p>
            <ul class="ref-step-list">
              <li>Finally, you can share personal thoughts based on previous steps.</li>
              <li>Do you like it? Why/why not? Again, use solid evidence to support your opinion.</li>
              <li>Is this piece effective? Is it saying what the artist is intending to say?</li>
              <li>Are you judging based on technique or emotional content? What criteria do <em>you</em> think are important when judging an artwork?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ref-depart">
        <p class="ref-depart-label">How Art Lab departs from this</p>
        <p>Art Lab replaces Step 4 (Judgment) with a Growth Path—shifting from aesthetic verdict to structural investigation. Step 3 (Interpretation) is held as hypothesis rather than conclusion, and the move from observation to interpretation now requires an Evidence Gate: enough structural observations must be mapped before interpretation is permitted. The framework also adds a Reflective Pause between Steps 2 and 3 to name the shift from automatic perception to judgment.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Visual Arts Standards -->
    <section class="ref-section">
      <div class="ref-section-header">
        <span class="ref-section-tag">Standards</span>
        <h2 class="ref-section-title">Visual Arts Standards</h2>
        <p class="ref-section-desc">The Elements of Art and Principles of Design form the baseline visual vocabulary used across educational frameworks, including the National Core Arts Standards. Art Lab analysis prompts use this vocabulary as the observational foundation for Step 1 and Step 2.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ref-standards-grid">
        <div class="ref-standard-block">
          <h3 class="ref-standard-title">Elements of Art</h3>
          <p class="ref-standard-note">The building blocks — what is physically present in the work</p>
          <ul class="ref-standard-list">
            <li><strong>Color</strong> — hue, value, saturation, temperature, relationships between colors</li>
            <li><strong>Line</strong> — direction, weight, quality, implied vs. actual</li>
            <li><strong>Shape</strong> — geometric vs. organic, positive vs. negative</li>
            <li><strong>Texture</strong> — actual (physical surface) vs. implied (visual representation)</li>
            <li><strong>Form</strong> — three-dimensional volume; depth in two-dimensional work</li>
            <li><strong>Space</strong> — positive/negative, depth, perspective, figure-ground</li>
            <li><strong>Value</strong> — light and dark; the range from white to black</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ref-standard-block">
          <h3 class="ref-standard-title">Principles of Design</h3>
          <p class="ref-standard-note">How elements are organized — what the work is doing with what's there</p>
          <ul class="ref-standard-list">
            <li><strong>Balance</strong> — visual weight distribution; symmetrical, asymmetrical, radial</li>
            <li><strong>Emphasis</strong> — focal point; what draws and holds attention</li>
            <li><strong>Movement</strong> — how the eye travels through the composition</li>
            <li><strong>Pattern</strong> — repetition of elements creating visual rhythm</li>
            <li><strong>Repetition</strong> — recurring elements that create unity</li>
            <li><strong>Proportion</strong> — size relationships between elements</li>
            <li><strong>Rhythm</strong> — visual beat created by repeated elements with variation</li>
            <li><strong>Unity</strong> — the sense that all elements belong together</li>
            <li><strong>Variety</strong> — difference and contrast that creates visual interest</li>
            <li><strong>Contrast</strong> — difference between elements; drives emphasis and edge detection</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Master Project Bible -->
    <section class="ref-section ref-section--forthcoming">
      <div class="ref-section-header">
        <span class="ref-section-tag">Framework</span>
        <h2 class="ref-section-title">Master Project Bible</h2>
        <p class="ref-section-desc">The full Hidden Grammar framework documentation — 11 Roots, 54 Principles, 4 Poles, and the structural logic connecting them. This section will consolidate the complete specification in one place.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ref-forthcoming-links">
        <p class="ref-forthcoming-note">The framework is currently documented across several pages:</p>
        <div class="ref-link-list">
          <a href="/hidden-grammar/framework" class="ref-link-card">
            <span class="ref-link-title">Art Lab Framework</span>
            <span class="ref-link-desc">Structural overview — 11 Roots, 54 Principles, 4 Poles</span>
            <span class="ref-link-arrow">→</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/hidden-grammar/principles" class="ref-link-card">
            <span class="ref-link-title">54 Principles</span>
            <span class="ref-link-desc">Complete inventory by tier with mechanism descriptions</span>
            <span class="ref-link-arrow">→</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/hidden-grammar/lenses" class="ref-link-card">
            <span class="ref-link-title">Interrogation Lenses</span>
            <span class="ref-link-desc">24 critical and philosophical frameworks as analytical overlays</span>
            <span class="ref-link-arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</HiddenGrammarLayout>

<style>
  .ref-page {
    max-width: 860px;
  }

  .ref-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .ref-label {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #64748b;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .ref-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .ref-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: #475569;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  /* ── Sections ───────────────────────────────── */
  .ref-section {
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f5f9;
  }

  .ref-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .ref-section-header {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .ref-section-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #64748b;
    background: #f1f5f9;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
  }

  .ref-section-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin: 0 0 0.625rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  }

  .ref-section-desc {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #64748b;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  /* ── Feldman steps ──────────────────────────── */
  .ref-steps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .ref-step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .ref-step:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .ref-step-num {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 1.25rem 0 0;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #cbd5e1;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .ref-step-body {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .ref-step-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }

  .ref-step-note {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: #94a3b8;
    margin: 0 0 0.875rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .ref-step-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0 0 0 1.125rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.375rem;
  }

  .ref-step-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #334155;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .ref-step-aside {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #64748b;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
    font-style: italic;
    padding-left: 1.125rem;
    border-left: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .ref-depart {
    background: #f8fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .ref-depart-label {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #94a3b8;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .ref-depart p:last-child {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #475569;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Standards grid ─────────────────────────── */
  .ref-standards-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .ref-standard-block {
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.375rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .ref-standard-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }

  .ref-standard-note {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #94a3b8;
    margin: 0 0 0.875rem;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .ref-standard-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0 0 0 1.125rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.375rem;
  }

  .ref-standard-list li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #334155;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* ── Forthcoming / Master Project Bible ─────── */
  .ref-section--forthcoming .ref-section-title {
    color: #64748b;
  }

  .ref-forthcoming-note {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #94a3b8;
    margin: 0 0 0.875rem;
  }

  .ref-link-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.625rem;
  }

  .ref-link-card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto auto;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-decoration: none;
    background: #ffffff;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, box-shadow 0.15s ease;
  }

  .ref-link-card:hover {
    border-color: #94a3b8;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  }

  .ref-link-title {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0f172a;
  }

  .ref-link-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: #94a3b8;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .ref-link-arrow {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #4f46e5;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ─────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .ref-standards-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .ref-link-card {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    }

    .ref-link-desc {
      display: none;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .ref-step {
      grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr;
    }

    .ref-step-num {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }

    .ref-step-body {
      padding: 1rem 1rem 1rem 0;
    }
  }
</style>
